          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/by Authors/.The Measurements of Proton Total Reaction",
                "Cross Sections is Carried Out in these Experiments by",
                "Recording Anticoincidences Between Passing and Stopping",
                "Counters to Measure the Beam Attenuation.",
                "Measurements were Made For the Four Positions of the",
                "Energy-Reducing Foil Marked a,B,C and D."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "/by Authors/.The Quantity Obtained Directly From the",
                "Data is the Experimental Value of Nx*Sigma(R*),Where",
                "Nx is the Number of Nuclei Per Cm**2 in the Attenuator",
                "and Sigma(R*) Is the Experimental Total Reaction Cross",
                "Section of these Nuclei For 29 MeV Protons.The Quantity",
                "Nx is Obtained to an Error of About 1% by Measuring the",
                "Mass and Area of Each Attenuator.The Total Reaction",
                "Cross Section Sigma(R) Is Obtained From Sigma(R*) By",
                "Applying the Elastic and Inelastic Scattering",
                "Corrections."
              ]
            }
          ],
